  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In term of API naming for the multi indices feature what we have today on react-is: \r\n\r\n* connectAutocomplete: a connector that have the query (and can refine on it) and all the hits. \r\n* index: to specify stuff related to one index in particular (could be any widgets here, of search parameters). \r\n\r\nThe way we use it:\r\n\r\n* Autocomplete use case => usage of connectAutoComplete\r\n* Displaying hits from different indices => usage of Index. \r\n\r\nHope that helps to make a naming choice. I'd love to have similar connectors whenever possible. ",
    "created_at": "2018-01-12T15:04:29Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2651#issuecomment-357261685",
